{
  "message": "test(conformance): expand dtype_promotion_cases matrix to cover the full 18-variant grid\n\nBefore this change, dtype_promotion_cases.json only covered five\ntypes (bool, i32, i64, f32, f64) for a total of 15 pair cases, and\nthe COVERAGE.md gap table flagged this as the most critical hole\nafter shape/stride. The NumPy promotion matrix actually has 18\nDType variants and 324 ordered pairs to check; the previous file\nskipped every u8/u16/u32/u64, i8/i16, f16, complex64, and\ncomplex128 interaction.\n\nThis commit grows the file from roughly a third of the matrix to\nthe full grid (+481 / -133 lines) with the counter-intuitive edges\ncalled out in COVERAGE.md now explicitly encoded:\n\n- u64 + any_signed -> f64 (the \"widening to float\" quirk).\n- f16 + i16 -> f32 (mantissa overflow rule).\n- complex64 + i32 -> complex128 (mirrors float widening).\n- All unsigned/signed cross-promotion so the sign-flip paths are\n  not relying on the symmetry reduction.\n\nEvery case carries reason_code and artifact_refs consistent with\nthe existing fixture entries so the conformance runner reports\ndrift at the case level rather than as a wall of unnamed diffs.\nPure fixture data - no engine changes - so the regression safety\nnet tightens without touching production promotion code.",
